Implementing a spike right now:

### Given
```java
	// Since 5.4 you may return a single dynamic test.
	@TestFactory
	DynamicTest dynamicNodeSingle() {
		return dynamicTest("single dynamic test", () -> assertFalse(false));
	}

	// Since 5.4 you may also return a single dynamic container.
	@TestFactory
	DynamicContainer dynamicNodeTree() {
		return dynamicContainer("single dynamic container", Stream.of(
			dynamicTest("foo", () -> assertTrue(true)),
			dynamicTest("bar", () -> assertFalse(false))
		));
	}
```

### Then A
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2319838/45908122-23364400-bdfb-11e8-904f-f124fae1f460.png)

### Then B
```
> single dynamic test
> single dynamic container
  > foo
  > bar
```
_without the method node_


Which one do you want?
